@page "/"

<PageTitle>ClaimsChat</PageTitle>

<h1>ClaimsChat</h1>

<p>
    A small demo app for chatting with claims documents. This is the workshop's
    teaching vehicle — browse the <a href="documents">Documents</a>, then ask
    questions on the <a href="chat">Chat</a> page.
</p>

<p>
    On <a href="chat">Chat</a>, lexical retrieval ranks the seeded claim documents
    for your question, feeds the most relevant ones to an Azure OpenAI model, and
    streams back a grounded answer with its sources. It answers about individual
    claims (cause of loss, damages, coverage, financials) — not totals across all
    claims. Try a suggested-question chip to start.
</p>

<p class="muted">
    The retrieval and AI client are a sealed box; the ordinary app around them is
    the teachable surface. No AI key configured? The Chat page falls back to a stub
    model so the app still runs end-to-end.
</p>
